## ðŸ“– Overview

**Minishell** is a minimalist implementation of a Unix shell inspired by **bash**.  
The goal of this project is to understand and recreate the core behavior of a shell by handling:

- Process creation
- File descriptors
- Pipes & redirections
- Environment variables
- Signals

This project is part of the **42 School curriculum**.

---

## âœ¨ Features

- ðŸ”¹ Command execution with `PATH` resolution
- ðŸ”¹ Built-in commands
- ðŸ”¹ Pipes (`|`)
- ðŸ”¹ Redirections:
  - Input `<`
  - Output `>`
  - Append `>>`
  - Heredoc `<<`
- ðŸ”¹ Environment variable expansion (`$VAR`, `$?`)
- ðŸ”¹ Signal handling (`Ctrl+C`, `Ctrl+D`, `Ctrl+\`)
- ðŸ”¹ Quote handling (`'`, `"`)
- ðŸ”¹ Interactive prompt with history (GNU Readline)

---

## ðŸ§° Built-in Commands

| Command  | Description |
|--------|------------|
| `echo` | Display a line of text |
| `cd`   | Change directory |
| `pwd`  | Print working directory |
| `export` | Set environment variables |
| `unset`  | Remove environment variables |
| `env`  | Display environment |
| `exit` | Exit the shell |

